A 20 mm depressed lesion in the ascending colon was resected in 17 minutes using TECS, and the mucosal defect was 35 mm × 30 mm. (
Fig. 2
) Mucosal defect closure was performed using a TECS-based clip closure (
Video 1
). The operator used SureClip Plus (Micro-Tech Co. Ltd.) to grasp and elevate the muscular layer of the mucosal defect while folding it. The assistant then used SureClip Eco to secure the mucosa, muscularis, and mucosa layers, ensuring proper closure. This process was repeated multiple times. After achieving partial closure, the operator and assistant alternated applying additional clips to reduce closure time. Complete closure was achieved within 19 minutes (
Fig. 3
).
